correction_response:
This tweet is misinformed. According to multiple sources, Roseanne Boyland was not beaten to death by Officer Lila Morris or any other officer. She was reportedly trampled to death by fellow protesters during the Capitol riot. There's no evidence to suggest that Officer Morris was involved in her death. Please refer to these sources for accurate information: 
https://www.medpagetoday.com/washington-watch/electioncoverage/90559
https://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/us-capitol-riot-woman-killed-was-a-pro-trumper-sucked-in-by-qanon-conspiracy-theory/GG2FXVYCKB3YFUGCLXLQJ2224E/
note_1_text: Rosanne Boyland died of a methamphetamine overdose and had a history of drug convictions. Her death was not due to police violence or trampling by a crowd.    https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/capitol-riot-death-drug-overdose-b1828539.html?amp  https://www.newsweek.com/fact-check-there-new-footage-showing-police-beating-rioter-rosanne-boyland-1653492  https://www.thedailybeast.com/capitol-rioter-rosanne-boyland-died-from-acute-amphetamine-intoxication
note_2_text: According to the medical examiner, Rosanne Boyland died of an acute methamphetamine overdose during the Capitol insurrection. She was not beaten to death and targeting a police officer like this is not great. https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/capitol-riot-death-drug-overdose-b1828539.html?amp
